      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IMPRESS WILDER (4) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when seventh at this track over 488m behind Chicken Fish (28.62) in a Grade 5/6. Was in the money prior to that. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Has ability and looks hard to stop. MASQUERADE PARTY (1) was game in defeat at the latest run, finishing second and beaten a neck (27.94) behind Impress Seminyak at this track. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Can feature again. SUNSET PARIS (7) was in the minors two back (28.15) at this track but ran below best last time there, finishing 6th. Form here at the trip sound including three wins. Form is hard to fault from this box, with a win and two minor placings from three starts. Key runner on best form. IMPRESS BUGSY (3) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.",
